text.tspan: Your Commitment to
Train with
Boothby Performance
BioMechanical Testing
Our training philosophy focuses on the
development of proper building blocks. In order to
create a strong foundation we have created a
prerequisite bio-mechanical test to direct your
assigned training. The data is used to customize
your training in order to address injury risk factors
and movement dysfunction.
Performance
Testing
After you commit to our training methodology,
you will need to decide how frequently you will
train. Training is usually between 2 and 4 days
per week. Our training programs are developed
in 4 week blocks. Most athletes register 4, 8 or
12 weeks at a time. We are now offering our
Academy program, which is a year round
program.
Test Evaluations
and Prescription
After your test, you will receive your SnapShot Report and Husky
Homework. The SnapShot is a visual representation of your
Bio-Mechanical Testing â€“ you can schedule a consultation with a
trainer to review! The Husky Homework is your at home prescriptive
training program. It improves your bio-mechanical and neuromuscu
lar function as well as your Energy System Development (ESD).
For athletes who are ready for our advanced training
levels, performance testing is used to assign intensity
levels. These tests assure that we track performance
outputs and optimize the training process in the pursuit of
elite results! (Not all athletes are immediately eligible for
Performance Testing)
We have broken training into 4 main levels â€“ Capacity, Endurance,
Strength and Power. If you have current injuries or demonstrate
high risk, your training will be replaced with advanced care and
rehabilitation. Capacity Athletes will work on their corrective
movements and ESD at the gym until they are ready to complete
these at home. Endurance, Strength and Power athletes will
receive a customized training program that is most often performed
at a Boothby Performance Center.
Boothby Performanceâ€™s training method is built
around the idea of improvement and adaptation.
We encourage all of our athletes to retest every 8
weeks in order to get the best results. By updating
your bio-mechanical and performance test results,
we provide the most optimized training program for
every athlete and mitigate risk of injury.
Whether your goals involve health and wellness, the
weekend 5K, a co-ed soccer game, getting
recruited to play in college, or getting drafted into
the pros, our final step â€“ Launch! â€“ is geared
towards your needs. For recruits and draftees, we
provide custom testing and complete reports
outlining athlete tests, training, and combine results.
